com.jayway.changeless.sequences
Class SequenceSupport<T>

java.lang.Object
  com.jayway.changeless.sequences.SequenceSupport<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of the elements in this sequence.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Sequence<T>, Sequenceable<T>, Iterable<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
LazySequence
public abstract class SequenceSupport<T>
extends Object
implements Sequence<T>

A support class for implementing sequences. The only method you have to implement is Sequence.first() and Sequence.rest()

reduce

public <R> R reduce(R start,
                    Fn2<? super R,? super T,R> function)
Description copied from interface: Sequence

Reduces this sequence into a accumulated result by calling the given function on each element of the sequence starting with the provided start value. Reducing a sequence of the elements 1, 2, and 3 with the plus-function staring from zero, will result in the following evaluation:

plus(plus(plus(0, 1), 2) 3)

Specified by:
reduce in interface Sequence<T>
Type Parameters:
R - The type of the accumulated value.
Parameters:
start - The base value for the calculation.
function - The accumulation function.
Returns:
The accumulated value.

zip

public <TOther> Sequence<Tuple<T,TOther>> zip(Sequence<TOther> sequence)
Description copied from interface: Sequence

Zips the elements of this sequence and the given sequence into a lazy sequence of tuples.

Example: 

 
 s1 = Sequences.of(1,2,3,4);
 s2 = Sequences.of(5,6,7,8,9,10);
 actual = s1.zip(s2);
 expected = Sequences.of(Tuples.of(1,5),
                         Tuples.of(2,6),
                         Tuples.of(3,7),
                         Tuples.of(4,8));
 assertEquals(expected, actual);
 
 
 






Specified by:
zip in interface Sequence<T>






Type Parameters:
TOther - the element type of the given sequence.
Parameters:
sequence - the sequence to be zipped together with this sequence.

Returns:
the zipped sequence.

insertAt

public Sequence<T> insertAt(int index,
                            T... elements)
Description copied from interface: Sequence
Returns a new sequence where the given elements are inserted at index in this sequence. If index is negative the given elements are inserted at the front of this sequence. If the index is larger than the the size of this sequence the given elements are inserted at the end of this sequence.

Specified by:
insertAt in interface Sequence<T>
Parameters:
index - the index the elements should be inserted at in this sequence.
elements - the elements to be inserted.
Returns:
the sequence with the elements inserted.
